          </setup>
          <statement>
            <p><m>f(x) = \sin(x)</m>;<m>c=0</m></p>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <p>All derivatives of <m>\sin(x)</m> are either <m>\pm\cos(x)</m> or <m>\pm \sin(x)</m>, which evaluate to <m>\pm 1</m> or <m>0</m> at <m>x=0</m>. The Taylor series starts <m>0+x+0x^2-\frac16x^3+0x^4+\frac1{120}x^5</m>;</p>

            <p>the Taylor series is <m>\ds \infser[0] (-1)^n\frac{x^{2n+1}}{(2n+1)!}</m></p>
