            <p><m>f^{(n)}(x) = (-1)^{n+1}\frac{n!}{(x+1)^{n+1}}</m>; at <m>x=1</m>, <m>f^{(n)}(1)=(-1)^{n+1}\frac{n!}{2^{n+1}}</m></p>

            <p>The Taylor series starts <m>\frac12+\frac14(x-1)-\frac18(x-1)^2+\frac1{16}(x-1)^3\cdots</m>;</p>

